abstract: The Japanese unit of UBS is expected to plead guilty to a criminal charge in the investigation into rate rigging. | The delay in SolarCity's I.P.O. didn't dissuade investors on the company's first day of trading. | Yahoo continues its effort to remake itself, adding a co-founder of PayPal to its board. | Richard Perry, the hedge fund manager whose firm took a majority stake in Barneys New York, lives in style.

headline.main: Guilty Plea Expected for UBS Unit in Rate-Rigging Case
